  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Localised preparedness and response to primary and secondary impacts of COVID-19 in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1-By implementing this program spread of the Covid-19, morbidity and mortality rates will be decrease through engaging faith leaders, key influencers, health workers, youth/community structures raising awareness to prevention infection, messaging in local languages to address rumours and stigma using traditional community structures CDC, local radio and TV stations). Enhancing minimum handwashing hygiene standards.
2 &#x2013; Access to basic non-Covid related health services by vulnerable group is sustained.
3- Food Security of vulnerable households safeguarded from economic impact due to containment measures.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ob1-A1-Community level awareness raising through Posters, Public announcements, religious actors, radio-TV messages, mass-SMS to prevent and control COVID-19 and decrease VAWG (M1-5).
2-WASH Support: hygiene kits (WASH cluster standards) and hygiene promotion. (M2-4) 1000 HH.
3- Engage faith leaders, key influencers, health workers, youth &amp; existing community structures for awareness raising on infection prevention and control (M2-5)
Ob2
A4- Access to healthcare and psychosocial support: Psychosocial support and counselling to the families of infected people as well as referral service to patients with suspected infection through Community Youth Volunteer Groups. (M1-5)

Ob3, A5- Need assessment: Conduct detailed assessment in targeted communities, IDP camps and Urban areas to identify the most vulnerable people. (M1).
A6- Nutrition Support: Distribution infant food packs, malnourished children u-7, pregnant lactating mothers. (M2-4).
A7- Social protection and safety-net approaches: Distribution of standard food package: - Wheat Flour, Local Rice, Vegetable Oil, Pulses, Salt, Sugar, (Total cost 86 USD + -10%). This will be especially for 1) extremely poor, 3) disabled, 4) aged, 5) single women headed households (M2-4)</narrative>
  </description>
